The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of a graph contraction problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithm design. The problem is studied in the context of a family of graphs that generalizes the family of trees, which is a well-studied topic in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
